  "text": "In one of recognition study by Nghi and Yecenia [CITATION_1] on the IT employees, the study discovered that successful practices, where providing a persistent and accurate feedback to IT staff, recognition and noticeable rewards develops the teamwork spirit, and makes an achievement of balance between an individual's professional and personal identity. Recognition and appreciation systems are an important part of the change that is necessary for any transformation to be effective. A thorough rethinking and restructuring of recognition and appreciation practices which are aligned with new organizational goals and culture will give companies the focused energy they will need to succeed in challenging times. Those companies that use relevant compensation and rewards as strategic resource tools will be able to realize the tremendous potential of their employees, working together.",
